---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Bio — Bradley Davis"
  current="bio"
  description="Bradley Davis's career story: from oilfield field engineer to senior backend engineer to AI-native builder."
>
  <div class="hero">
    <picture>
      <source
        type="image/webp"
        srcset="/images/headshot-88.webp 1x, /images/headshot-176.webp 2x, /images/headshot-264.webp 3x"
      />
      <img
        class="headshot"
        src="/images/headshot-176.jpg"
        width="88"
        height="88"
        alt=""
      />
    </picture>
    <h1>Bio</h1>
  </div>

  <p class="lede">
    Senior backend engineer turned AI-native builder. Seven years shipping
    production payment and platform systems before pivoting into agentic
    engineering full time.
  </p>

  <p>
    I got here sideways. Before software, I supervised measurement-while-drilling
    operations on oil rigs, wrote coreboot and UEFI firmware for embedded x86
    boards, and prototyped an ELK-stack log pipeline for Cray's HPC systems. A
    master's in computer science at UW-Madison (distributed systems, machine
    learning, big data) turned that detour into a real engineering career:
    three years on QuickBooks' webhooks infrastructure at Intuit (10-20M
    notifications a day at 99.9% reliability), then four years on OKX's fiat
    payments platform (30+ payment providers across APAC, EU, and the US),
    where I led the platform's largest architectural effort.
  </p>

  <p>
    I left OKX in May 2026, and I have used the time since to go all-in on
    the shift I already saw coming: agentic engineering. MCP servers, multi-agent
    orchestration, LLM-app architecture, the patterns that hold up outside a
    demo. I run all of it off a five-machine, Nix-managed homelab (Caddy
    reverse proxy, self-hosted git, Pi-hole DNS, Home Assistant, ZFS-replicated
    storage) that doubles as a daily proving ground for whatever I am building.
  </p>

  <p>
    Off the keyboard: an Eagle Scout who once saved a life with CPR, a
    former ski instructor, and two small kids.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Full history on the <a href="/resume">resume</a>. Reach me at
    <a href="mailto:hire@bdavis.ai">hire@bdavis.ai</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
